{"GUID":"1730fa74-a66c-4348-8acb-f055abc2a2bc","Type":"Text","Text":"Joel Christner 2611 Raleigh Way, El Dorado Hills CA 95762 USA | (408) 396-3007 joel.christner@gmail.com | www.joelchristner.com | github | linkedin OBJECTIVE Executive technologist and open source developer with proven history disrupting markets and building businesses to a successful outcome. Seeking challenges that require elegant technology solutions to drive market leadership or create new technology categories.
EXPERIENCE 3/2019 – Present Dell Technologies www.dell.com Director and Distinguished Engineer Round Rock, TX Responsible for technology strategy, research, and development in domains critical to the future success of the company including distributed systems, serverless computing, data management, data virtualization, disintermediation, advanced compression, and as-a- service. Served as an advisor to executive leadership including the CEO, COO, and CTO on technology strategy. 5/2017 – 3/2019 CloudGenix, Inc. (acquired by Palo Alto Networks) www.cloudgenix.com Vice President, Marketing San Jose, CA Pioneered the Software-Defined Wide Area Networking (SD-WAN) category, re-established the company brand and entire collateral portfolio, successfully created the company’s first end-to-end marketing funnel, and facilitated revenue growth by 500% leading to a successful acquisition and creation of the Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) category. 12/2014 – 5/2017 Cake, Corp. (acquired by Sysco Foods) www.trycake.com Chief Architect Redwood City, CA Designed and built the payments and settlement infrastructure used by tens of thousands of merchants driving tens of billions of dollars in payment volume annually. 12/2011 – 12/2014 Cube, Co. (acquired by Rocket Lawyer) www.getcube.com Co-founder, Chief Technology Officer Mountain View, CA Owned and managed technology strategy and implementation for the emerging payments as-a-service category including mobile card terminals, mobile point of sale, developer APIs for in-person and online card processing. Scaled the platform to support thousands of merchants and hundreds of developers including marquee brands. 8/2009 – 12/2011 StorSimple, Inc. (acquired by Microsoft) www.storsimple.com Distinguished Engineer and Chief Scientist Santa Clara, CA Led solution architecture and product management while creating the cloud storage controller category, and created a product competing with industry behemoths that grew to tens of millions in annual revenue, a recognized market leadership position with multiple industry analysts, and a successful exit with Microsoft. 8/2008 – 8/2009 Cisco Systems, Inc. www.cisco.com Technical Leader San Jose, CA Drove the widespread integration of application delivery capabilities directly into core networking platforms (routers, switches) and the integration of several disparate technologies into a unified architecture for application delivery. 7/2007 – 8/2008 Reconnex Corporation (acquired by McAfee) www.reconnex.net Director, Product Management Mountain View, CA Pioneered the Data Loss Prevention (DLP) market including data-in-use, data-in-motion, and data-at-rest. Grew revenue by 400% leading to the acquisition by and integration into McAfee. 12/2002 – 7/2007 Cisco Systems, Inc. www.cisco.com Sr Manager, Technical Marketing, Application Delivery San Jose, CA Pioneered the WAN optimization and application acceleration category, leading to hundreds of millions in annual revenue and recognized leadership positions by Gartner, Forrester, IDC, and other analysts.
AREAS OF EXPERTISE Leadership of geographically distributed teams in domains of engineering, software development, and research. Fluent in full-stack multi-platform development and proficient in multiple languages (C#, Java, Javascript, more). Focus areas are API platforms, distributed systems, networking, databases, data storage, messaging, information search and retrieval, deduplication, cloud infrastructure, cloud-native architectures, serverless, and emerging data storage media.
EDUCATION 1/2007 – 7/2010 Columbia University, MS Computer Science www.columbia.edu New York City, NY
PATENTS More than two dozen patents pending in the domains of data management, distributed systems, serverless computing, cloud-native architectures, and security. Patents granted include: 8,667,121 System and Method for Managing Data and Policies 8,850,591 System and Method for Concept Building 11,394,397 System and Method for Selecting Lossless Compression Algorithm Considering User SLAs 11,360,968 System and Method for Identification of Access Patterns
MISCELLANEOUS Open source author and package maintainer (>1K stars on Github, >4M downloads on NuGet) Chairperson for the Storage Networking Industry Association (SNIA) workgroup on DNA Data Storage Previously held numerous industry certifications including Cisco CCIE (#15311), Microsoft MCSE Active Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu (BJJ) practitioner and coach
REFERENCES Excellent professional and personal references from a number of industries are available upon request.","ChunkingConfiguration":{"Strategy":"FixedTokenCount","FixedTokenCount":192,"OverlapCount":0,"OverlapStrategy":"SlidingWindow","RowGroupSize":5},"EmbeddingConfiguration":{"EmbeddingEndpointId":"default","L2Normalization":true}}
